  section.container 
      h3.content__title Common questions about home security systems and alarm monitoring 
      h4.content__subtitle How much do alarm systems cost?
      p.content__text For many people, the price of a home security system is one of the most important factors in deciding which alarm system to purchase. There are four basic elements to consider: upfront (installation) costs, ongoing (monthly) subscription costs, equipment costs and municipal fees. Be aware that many home insurance providers offer discounts (up to 20 percent) for homes with monitored alarm systems.
      .content__table 
        .content__table-row 
          .content__table-title Upfront Cost:
          .content__table-description 
            p.content__text Installation is either professional or do-it-yourself (DIY); some companies let you choose an installation method, while others offer only one option. Professional installation costs can run $100-$500+; DIY is free, but it requires more of the consumer’s time.
        .content__table-row 
          .content__table-title Subscription cost:
          .content__table-description 
            p.content__text Subscription security systems – home alarms monitored 24/7 by outside companies – carry a monthly fee, usually in the $20-$60 range.
